definition[0]: if something warps, or if heat or cold warps it, it becomes bent or twisted, and loses its original shape
example[0]: The door must be warped. It won’t close properly.
definition[1]: to influence someone in a way that has a harmful effect on how they think or behave
example[1]: You mustn’t allow your dislike of her to warp your judgment.
definition[2]: a part of something that has become bent or twisted from its original shape
